definition: Songliao Plain of northeast China including Songhua River 松花江 through the Liaoning Peninsula, also called the Northeast Plain 東北平原|东北平原[Dong1 bei3 Ping2 yuan2]
short name for Liaoning 遼寧|辽宁[Liao2 ning2] province/Liao or Khitan dynasty (907-1125)
flat/level/equal/to tie (make the same score)/to draw (score)/calm/peaceful/see also 平聲|平声[ping2 sheng1]

sentences.english: The Songliao plain is a basin in both topography and geology.
sentences.chinese: 松遼平原在地貌和地質上都是一個盆地。

sentences.english: Changling County is located at the west of Jilin Province, the hinterland of Songliao Plain.
sentences.chinese: 長嶺縣位於吉林省西部，松遼平原腹地。
